## Implementation Guide

### Step 1: Add Physics Implementation

Edit the scheme files to implement the actual physics:

```fortran
! In schemes/{{ process_name }}{{ schemes[0]|title if schemes }}Scheme_Mod.F90
subroutine {{ schemes[0] if schemes else 'calculate' }}(container, process, rc)
  ! Add your physics calculations here

  ! Example: Get meteorological data
  met_state => container%get_met_state_ptr()
  temperature => met_state%get_field('temperature')

  ! Example: Get chemistry data
  chem_state => container%get_chem_state_ptr()
  concentrations => chem_state%get_concentrations()

  ! Implement your calculations...

end subroutine
```

### Step 2: Add Process Parameters

Define process-specific parameters in the init routine:

```fortran
subroutine {{ process_name|lower }}_init(this, container, rc)
  ! Read configuration parameters
  call container%get_config_value('processes.{{ process_name|lower }}.parameters.example_param', &
                                  this%example_param, default_value, rc)

  ! Validate parameters
  if (this%example_param < 0.0) then
    call error_manager%log_error('Invalid parameter value')
    rc = 1
    return
  end if
end subroutine
```

### Step 3: Add Diagnostics

Register diagnostic outputs:

```fortran
! Register diagnostic fields
call container%get_diagnostic_manager_ptr() => diag_mgr
call diag_mgr%register_field('{{ process_name|lower }}_rate', &
                           'Process rate', 'units', field_dims)
```

